a722 4
We rotate |a| so that |ah| is at the bottom, \ie, its |y| coordinate
is the least of any |y| coordinate of points in |a|.
We have some freedom in picking the angle to rotate by.  
At one extreme, angle |alpha| lays the vector from |ah->prev| to |ah| at angle
d725 1
a725 9
lays the vector from |ah| to |ah->next| at angle 0.

We randomly choose an angle from a uniform distribution over $[\alpha,\beta]$.

Just for now, I've introduced |prev_bias|, which is the fraction from 
0 through 1 
specifying how much we 
should make the |ah->prev| to |ah| vector lay flat at 0 degrees, as 
opposed to laying the |ah| to |ah->next| vector lay flat at 0 degrees.
d727 1
d738 8
a745 4

