@@ All the valid components are in the initial part of the |component| array.
d173 13
a185 13
This procedure tricky only because the components must be distinct.
The second component is selected with replacement and discarded if
we're so unlucky as to get the same component as we first picked.
The expected number of iterations is |1+1/(num_components-1)|.

@@<Module subroutines@@>=
static void
get_component_pair(component_t **a, component_t **b)
{
	*a = component + gb_unif_rand(component-next_component());
	do {
		*b = component + gb_unif_rand(component-next_component());
	} while( *a==*b );
